<h2>Nesting Tags</h2>
<p>You will obviously want to be able to make more complex tags, e.g. a link in bold text, which you do simply by placing the tag inside the contents of another tag:</p>

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint">
&lt;strong&gt;Bold statement but &lt;a href='http://example.com'&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; is better&lt;/strong&gt;</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="1">
    <strong>Bold statement but <a href="http://example.com">this is better</a></strong>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Div/Span</h2>
Divs and spans are just ways of grouping tags together so that they can be referenced from elsewhere (e.g. CSS which we will get to).  The &lt;div&gt; element is laid out like a block so starts a new line each time vs. &lt;span&gt; is laid out within the line.

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint">
&lt;div&gt;Each div&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;starts a&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;anew&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="1">
    <div>Each div</div><div>starts</div><div>anew</div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>vs.</p>

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint">
&lt;span&gt;But the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;spans span&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;across one line&lt;/span&gt;</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="1">
    <span>But the</span> <span>spans span</span> <span>across one line</span>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Comments</h2>

Comments are special, but they&#039;re pretty simple.  They get ignored by the browser but show up in the code.  Starts with &lt;!-- and ends with --&gt;.

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint">
&lt;!-- hi there, no-one can see me --&gt;</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="1">
    <!-- hi there, no-one can see me --></span>
  </div>
</div>

